.TH "nx842_OF_upd_maxsglen" 9 "nx842_OF_upd_maxsglen" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nx842_OF_upd_maxsglen \- - Update the device info from OF maxsglen prop
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nx842_OF_upd_maxsglen
.BI "(struct nx842_devdata *devdata "  ","
.BI "struct property *prop "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "devdata" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "prop" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Definition of the 'ibm,max-sg-len' OF property:
This field indicates the maximum byte length of a scatter list
for the platform facility. It is a single cell encoded as with encode-int.

\fIdevdata\fP - struct nx842_devdata to update
\fIprop\fP - struct property point containing the maxsyncop for the update
.SH "EXAMPLE"
# od -x ibm,max-sg-len
0000000 0000 0ff0

In this example, the maximum byte length of a scatter list is
0x0ff0 (4,080).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success
-EINVAL on failure
